column2: General settings of Multiple Listings plugin. These settings affect all members in your community.

There settings applied per member level basic. If certain actions are not allowed for certain member level, users of said member level aren't able to perform them. Start by selecting member level you want to modify, then adjust the settings for that level below according to your preferences.

Your members can choose from any of the options checked below when they decide who can view their listings. If you do not check any options, settings will default to the last saved configuration. If you select only one option, members of this level will not have a choice.

Your members can choose from any of the options checked below when they decide who can comment on their listings. If you do not check any options, settings will default to the last saved configuration. If you select only one option, members of this level will not have a choice.

Your members can choose from any of the options checked below when they decide who can share their listings. If you do not check any options, settings will default to the last saved configuration. If you select only one option, members of this level will not have a choice.

Your members can choose from any of the options checked below when they decide who can add photos to their listings. If you do not check any options, settings will default to the last saved configuration. If you select only one option, members of this level will not have a choice.

Your members can choose from any of the options checked below when they decide who can add videos to their listings. If you do not check any options, settings will default to the last saved configuration. If you select only one option, members of this level will not have a choice.

Your members can choose from any of the options checked below when they decide who can add discussions to their listings. If you do not check any options, settings will default to the last saved configuration. If you select only one option, members of this level will not have a choice.
FAQs are effective in helping member to understand how things work. This page allows you to add and manage FAQs.
This place is to manage modules whose content could be imported as new listings. This feature allow you to add as many modules as you want.

This place is to manage quick links to some specific listings based on your criteria. You can add as many quick links as you need, them apply them to widget Listing Quick Links - Slideshow or Listing Quick Links - Link only. This feature is useful in case you want to introduce some listing to your users.

This is a place for you to change the appearance of listing types on listing menus. Each listing type has 3 sections: Top Categories, More Categories and Promotion Place where you have ability to change their content as your needs. By default, we pick 5 first categories of this listing type (including parent and sub categories) for both Top Categories and More Categories. We also add the default picture for Promotion Place.

Here is the place you can import listings from your excel file or from other modules. Please note the following rules about file format.
1. The order of columns in your excel file must be exactly matched with the order of default fields in creation form. It means first column is "Listing Title", the second is "Tags", then "Short Description", "Description", "About Us", "Price", "Location", "Location Longitude", "Location Latitude", the last is "Category and Sub - Category".
2. Listing Title and Short Description are required.
3. If the or category does not match any item on database, the corresponding listing will not be created.

Here is the place you can import listings from your excel file or from other modules. Please note the following rules about file format.
1. The order of columns in your excel file must be exactly matched with the order of default fields in creation form. It means first column is "Listing Title", the second is "Tags", then "Short Description", "Description", "About Us", "Price", "Location", "Location Longitude", "Location Latitude", "Category and Sub - Category", the last is "Listing Owner's Email".
2. Listing Title and Short Description are required.
3. If the email of listing owner or category does not match any item on database, the corresponding listing will not be created.

This place is for you to add many listing types such as: Antiques, Art, Books, Business, Real Estate, etc. In the listing types, you also need to add corresponding categories/sub categories as well as configure member level settings for theme. Each listing type has its own rating criteria for User/Editors reviews. You could add just a single Overall Rating criterion or you would create multiple rating criteria and the overall rating will automatically calculated as average of individual criteria.

Each listing type is a widgetized page and you can include more attractive widgets on it. Moreover, you can manage listings belong to the listing type and create as many Quick Links to specific listings as you want.

Are you sure you want to delete this listing type? All existing data such as categories, listings, rating criteria will be moved to another listing tpye. However, all member level settings as well as Listing Quick Links of this type will be deleted.

This page lists all listings avaiable on your site. There are several actions that can be performed such as View Details, Close, Open, Edit, Delete, Feature/Unfeature, Highlight and Import, in addition to several bulk actions.

Filter option provides Admin a quick way to sort through all listings available on your site.
